<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA04401D078F832FC5EF859" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[772,898,1987,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="81" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA04401D078F832FC5EF859" box="[772,898,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="81">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF03667EFFA14400D3EBF884FB27F87D" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6577765" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6577765" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6577765/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" startId="3.[151,264,1909,1933]" targetBox="[203,1386,181,1872]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA14400D3EBF884FB27F87D" blockId="3.[151,1437,1909,2041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D3EBF884FEE8F809" bold="true" box="[151,308,1909,1933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">FIGURES 1–8</emphasis>
. 1. 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D226F884FE19F80F" bold="true" box="[346,453,1909,1933]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">HOLOTYPE</emphasis>
♀ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA14400D296F884FC53F809" authority="J. Thomson, 1865" authorityName="J. Thomson" authorityYear="1865" box="[490,911,1909,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D296F884FD0EF809" box="[490,722,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Anhammus conspersus</emphasis>
J. Thomson, 1865
</taxonomicName>
, habitus (photo: G. Chemin); 2. ditto, labels (photo: G. Chemin); 3.= 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D244F868FE7FF82B" bold="true" box="[312,419,1945,1969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">HOLOTYPE</emphasis>
=♀ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA14400D2B9F868FCF2F835" authority="Pascoe, 1866" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[453,814,1945,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="licheneus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D2B9F868FD42F835" box="[453,670,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Nephelotus licheneus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA14400D1D9F868FCF2F835" author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[677,814,1945,1969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref4447" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a Descriptive Catalogue of the Species of the three Longicorn Families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. (Part III). The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 3 (3) 3, 225 - 336, pls X-XV." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, habitus (photo: BMNH); 4. ditto, labels (photo: BMNH); 5. ♂ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA14400D3CDF84CFE46F851" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[177,410,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D3CDF84CFE46F851" box="[177,410,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Nephelotus conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Sarawak (photo: BMNH); 6. ditto, labels (photo: BMNH); 7. 
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D737F84CFB69F857" bold="true" box="[1099,1205,1981,2005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">HOLOTYPE</emphasis>
♂ 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA14400D7A9F84CFEACF87D" authority="Newman, 1842" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monohammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA14400D7A9F84CFF10F87D" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="82">Monohammus marcipor</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFED4B07FFA14400D3AFF810FEACF87D" author="Newman, E." box="[211,368,2017,2041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="82" pagination="275 - 277" refId="ref4421" refString="Newman, E. (1842) Cerambycitum Insularum Manillarum Dom. Cuming captorum enumeratio digesta. The Entomologist, 17, 275 - 277." type="journal article" year="1842">Newman, 1842</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, habitus (photo: K. Matsumoto, BMNH); 8. ditto, labels (photo: K. Matsumoto, BMNH).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFF66FBF9FF35" blockId="4.[151,1159,151,249]" box="[151,1061,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
2) Antennomere III as long as IV (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D165FF66FD60FF35" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1944" box="[537,700,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D165FF66FD60FF35" box="[537,700,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Paranhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or longer than IV (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D0E2FF66FBC0FF35" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[926,1052,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D0E2FF66FBC0FF35" box="[926,1052,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFF4AFB5BFF51" blockId="4.[151,1159,151,249]" box="[151,1159,187,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
3) Mesosternum armed with a rounded tubercle (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D1C7FF4AFC82FF51" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1944" box="[699,862,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D1C7FF4AFC82FF51" box="[699,862,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Paranhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or unarmed (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D77CFF4AFBA2FF51" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[1024,1150,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D77CFF4AFBA2FF51" box="[1024,1150,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFF2EFBE3FF7D" blockId="4.[151,1159,151,249]" box="[151,1087,223,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
4) Pronotal base with three (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D2A9FF2EFDA4FF7D" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1944" box="[469,632,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Paranhammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D2A9FF2EFDA4FF7D" box="[469,632,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Paranhammus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) or two (
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D19EFF2EFCBCFF7D" authorityName=", Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[738,864,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D19EFF2EFCBCFF7D" box="[738,864,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) transverse furrows
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3EBFED0FB1CFE00" blockId="4.[151,1437,289,604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Actually, both genera have an open cicatrix, antennomere III about as long as IV, unarmed mesosternum and pronotal base with two large furrows. Only a specimen of Mindanao shows a supplementary incomplete superficial transverse impression between these furrows. Thus, all stated differential characters are untrue.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC336F6FFA64407D3BBFE7CFC78FDDF" blockId="4.[151,1437,289,604]" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D3BBFE7CFE09FE23" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" box="[199,469,397,423]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monohammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D3BBFE7CFE09FE23" box="[199,469,397,423]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Monohammus marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D171FE7CFCD2FE23" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[525,782,397,423]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D171FE7CFCD2FE23" box="[525,782,397,423]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Nephelotus conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show the same body structure and analogous pattern, differing little in antennal colour (dark brown in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D1C9FE43FCC0FE4F" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" box="[693,796,434,459]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monohammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D1C9FE43FCC0FE4F" box="[693,796,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and reddish testaceous in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D728FE43FB0CFE4F" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1108,1232,434,459]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D728FE43FB0CFE4F" box="[1108,1232,434,459]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and, maybe, the glabrous spot on the pronotal disc (rhomboidal in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D1B3FE27FCEAFE6B" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" box="[719,822,470,495]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monohammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D1B3FE27FCEAFE6B" box="[719,822,470,495]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and transverse in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D77AFE27FB5EFE6B" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1030,1154,470,495]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D77AFE27FB5EFE6B" box="[1030,1154,470,495]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both characters can be considered specific or even subspecific. The taxa are also biogeographically related since 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D7FFFE0BFB23FD97" baseAuthorityName="J. Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1155,1279,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Nephelotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="conspersus">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D7FFFE0BFB23FD97" box="[1155,1279,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">conspersus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7C4D75FFA64407D649FE0BFA40FD97" authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1842" box="[1333,1436,506,531]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monohammus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marcipor">
<emphasis id="B908EAE4FFA64407D649FE0BFA40FD97" box="[1333,1436,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">marcipor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seem to coexist in 
<collectingRegion id="49B8F814FFA64407D216FDECFE15FDB3" box="[362,457,541,567]" country="Philippines" name="Palawan" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Palawan</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry id="F36B7666FFA64407D2A4FDECFD86FDBC" box="[472,602,541,568]" name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="83">Philippines</collectingCountry>
). There is no substantial reason to consider them as belonging to different genera; consequently, the following taxonomic changes are proposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
